Please take our apologies if you receive this message more than once . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Call for Papers 3 rd Workshop on Information Systems Modelling ( ISM'2000 ) as a part of the MOSIS 2000 Conference Roznov pod Radhostem , Czech Republic , May , 2 - 4 , 2000 The workshop on Information Systems Modelling will be held as a part of 34 th MOSIS 2000 Conference in Roznov pod Radhostem on May 2 - 4 , 2000 . The purpose of the workshop is to promote discussion and interaction among members of the Information systems community with a special emphasis on models and modelling techniques . Program committee M . Bielikova , SK , A . Grzech , PL , P . Hanacek , CZ , T . Hruska , CZ , K . Jezek , CZ M . Lloyd- Williams , UK , N . Lorentzos , GR , Y . Manolopoulos , GR , P . Navrat , SK , J . Pokorny , CZ , P . Savino , IT , I . Vondrak , CZ , J . Zendulka , CZ , chair . Topics We invite the submission of original research contributions describing new results , original ideas and applications . The research should address issues concerning the theory , development , management and application of advanced information systems . In addition , we solicit contributions describing the development and maintenance of real systems . Suggested topics include , but are not limited to : - Application of Databases and Information Systems , - Business Process Modelling and Redesign , - Electronic Commerce Systems Development , - Database Theory and Design , - Data Mining and Knowledge Discovery , - Data , Process and Object Modelling , - Distributed and Web- Based Information Systems , - Formal Definition of Information Systems , - Information Privacy and Security , - Information Systems Development Methodology , Development Tools and Environments , - Information Systems Modelling in Education , - Information Warehousing and OLAP , - Object- Oriented Databases , - Temporal , Spatial , Active and Mobile Databases , - Text and Multimedia Databases , - Workflow Systems . Paper submission Send a full paper ( max . 6 pages in English ) in one of the following formats : plain Postscript file , MS Word 6 . 0 document , RTF file to the e-mail address : zendulka @ ykmmarua . ygyk . nd to be received by January 10 , 2000 . Papers submitted must be previously unpublished and not currently submitted for publication elsewhere . Papers will be evaluated by 3 reviewers . Authors will be notified of acceptance or rejection by February 21 , 2000 . A MS Word template file and a LaTeX style file for papers can be found on the workshop ? s home page address given below . Accepted papers will be published in a special volume of the MOSIS'2000 proceedings . Camera-ready versions in a specified format for the proceedings must be delivered both in an electronic and hard copy form due March 27 , 2000 .
